  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The field `drain_connections_on_host_removal` on the Cluster is poorly named as there are cases\r\nwhere endpoints are removed from a `HostSet` based on this field being set (ie active hc enabled, endpoint still healthy) without connections being drained (due to the somewhat recent batch update mechanism now supported by EDS).\r\n\r\nA better name might be `ignore_health_on_host_removal`, as this better describes that the option does without implying what the consequence of this is.",
